    public interface Object2ObjectMap<K,V>
extends Object2ObjectFunction<K,V>, java.util.Map<K,V>
    A type-specific Map; provides some additional methods that use polymorphism to avoid (un)boxing, and handling of a default return value.

    Besides extending the corresponding type-specific function, this interface strengthens Map.entrySet(), keySet() and values(). Maps returning entry sets of type Object2ObjectMap.FastEntrySet support also fast iteration.

    A submap or subset may or may not have an independent default return value (which however must be initialized to the default return value of the originator).
